{"key":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01|Gen|10","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Gen","chapter":10,"textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024","parserRevision":"v11","verses":[{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Gen:10:1","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Gen","bookOrder":0,"chapter":10,"verse":1,"text":"These are the family records of Noah’s sons, Shem, Ham, and Japheth. They also had sons after the flood.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Gen:10:2","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Gen","bookOrder":0,"chapter":10,"verse":2,"text":"Japheth’s sons: Gomer, Magog, Madai, Javan, Tubal, Meshech, and Tiras.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Gen:10:3","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Gen","bookOrder":0,"chapter":10,"verse":3,"text":"Gomer’s sons: Ashkenaz, Riphath, and Togarmah.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Gen:10:4","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Gen","bookOrder":0,"chapter":10,"verse":4,"text":"And Javan’s sons: Elishah, Tarshish, Kittim, and Dodanim.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Gen:10:5","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Gen","bookOrder":0,"chapter":10,"verse":5,"text":"From these descendants, the peoples of the coasts and islands spread out into their lands according to their clans in their nations, each with its own language.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Gen:10:6","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Gen","bookOrder":0,"chapter":10,"verse":6,"text":"Ham’s sons: Cush, Mizraim, Put, and Canaan.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Gen:10:7","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Gen","bookOrder":0,"chapter":10,"verse":7,"text":"Cush’s sons: Seba, Havilah, Sabtah, Raamah, and Sabteca. And Raamah’s sons: Sheba and Dedan.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Gen:10:8","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Gen","bookOrder":0,"chapter":10,"verse":8,"text":"Cush fathered Nimrod, who began to be powerful in the land.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Gen:10:9","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Gen","bookOrder":0,"chapter":10,"verse":9,"text":"He was a powerful hunter in the sight of the Lord. That is why it is said, “Like Nimrod, a powerful hunter in the sight of the Lord.”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Gen:10:10","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Gen","bookOrder":0,"chapter":10,"verse":10,"text":"His kingdom started with Babylon, Erech, Accad, and Calneh, in the land of Shinar.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Gen:10:11","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Gen","bookOrder":0,"chapter":10,"verse":11,"text":"From that land he went to Assyria and built Nineveh, Rehoboth-ir, Calah,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Gen:10:12","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Gen","bookOrder":0,"chapter":10,"verse":12,"text":"and Resen, between Nineveh and the great city Calah.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Gen:10:13","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Gen","bookOrder":0,"chapter":10,"verse":13,"text":"Mizraim fathered the people of Lud, Anam, Lehab, Naphtuh,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Gen:10:14","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Gen","bookOrder":0,"chapter":10,"verse":14,"text":"Pathrus, Casluh (the Philistines came from them), and Caphtor.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Gen:10:15","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Gen","bookOrder":0,"chapter":10,"verse":15,"text":"Canaan fathered Sidon his firstborn and Heth,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Gen:10:16","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Gen","bookOrder":0,"chapter":10,"verse":16,"text":"as well as the Jebusites, the Amorites, the Girgashites,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Gen:10:17","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Gen","bookOrder":0,"chapter":10,"verse":17,"text":"the Hivites, the Arkites, the Sinites,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Gen:10:18","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Gen","bookOrder":0,"chapter":10,"verse":18,"text":"the Arvadites, the Zemarites, and the Hamathites. Afterward the Canaanite clans scattered.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Gen:10:19","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Gen","bookOrder":0,"chapter":10,"verse":19,"text":"The Canaanite border went from Sidon going toward Gerar as far as Gaza, and going toward Sodom, Gomorrah, Admah, and Zeboiim as far as Lasha.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Gen:10:20","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Gen","bookOrder":0,"chapter":10,"verse":20,"text":"These are Ham’s sons by their clans, according to their languages, in their lands and their nations.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Gen:10:21","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Gen","bookOrder":0,"chapter":10,"verse":21,"text":"And Shem, Japheth’s older brother, also had sons. Shem was the father of all the sons of Eber.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Gen:10:22","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Gen","bookOrder":0,"chapter":10,"verse":22,"text":"Shem’s sons were Elam, Asshur, Arpachshad, Lud, and Aram.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Gen:10:23","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Gen","bookOrder":0,"chapter":10,"verse":23,"text":"Aram’s sons: Uz, Hul, Gether, and Mash.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Gen:10:24","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Gen","bookOrder":0,"chapter":10,"verse":24,"text":"Arpachshad fathered Shelah, and Shelah fathered Eber.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Gen:10:25","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Gen","bookOrder":0,"chapter":10,"verse":25,"text":"Eber had two sons. One was named Peleg, for during his days the earth was divided; his brother was named Joktan.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Gen:10:26","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Gen","bookOrder":0,"chapter":10,"verse":26,"text":"And Joktan fathered Almodad, Sheleph, Hazarmaveth, Jerah,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Gen:10:27","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Gen","bookOrder":0,"chapter":10,"verse":27,"text":"Hadoram, Uzal, Diklah,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Gen:10:28","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Gen","bookOrder":0,"chapter":10,"verse":28,"text":"Obal, Abimael, Sheba,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Gen:10:29","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Gen","bookOrder":0,"chapter":10,"verse":29,"text":"Ophir, Havilah, and Jobab. All these were Joktan’s sons.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Gen:10:30","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Gen","bookOrder":0,"chapter":10,"verse":30,"text":"Their settlements extended from Mesha to Sephar, the eastern hill country.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Gen:10:31","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Gen","bookOrder":0,"chapter":10,"verse":31,"text":"These are Shem’s sons by their clans, according to their languages, in their lands and their nations.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Gen:10:32","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Gen","bookOrder":0,"chapter":10,